# Feature / page composition

A feature page is a **layout of independent molecules**, not one mega-hook feeding every child via props.

## Correct shape

```
FeaturePage/
  FeaturePage.component.tsx          ← Provider + layout children only
  FeaturePage.context.tsx            ← page-wide shared state (if needed)
  molecules/
    FeatureMapSection/
      FeatureMapSection.component.tsx
      useFeatureMapSection.hook.ts   ← owns map-specific logic
    FeatureBottomSheet/
      FeatureBottomSheet.component.tsx
      useFeatureBottomSheet.hook.ts
  FeaturePageContent/
    FeaturePageContent.component.tsx ← thin layout shell
    FeaturePageContentV2.context.tsx ← sibling coordination (if needed)
    hooks/
      useFeaturePageContentV2State/  ← runs in Provider; coordination state only
      useFeaturePageContentV2Context/
    molecules/
      FeatureV2MapLayer/ + useFeatureV2MapLayer
      FeatureV2Header/   + useFeatureV2Header
      FeatureV2BottomSheet/ + useFeatureV2BottomSheet
```

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — page content is a layout shell; each child owns its hook
export const FeaturePageContentV2 = () => {
  const { mountContainerRef } = useFeaturePageContentV2Mount();
  return (
    <FeaturePageContentV2Provider>
      <div ref={mountContainerRef}>
        <FeatureV2MapLayer />
        <FeatureV2Header />
        <FeatureV2BottomSheet />
        <FeatureV2PlaceOverlay />
      </div>
    </FeaturePageContentV2Provider>
  );
};
```

## Forbidden patterns

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — god hook: one hook returns everything; parent prop-drills to children
export const FeaturePageContentV2 = () => {
  const { mapCenter, mapZoom, sheetRef, openSheet, filteredCities, selectedPlace, ... } =
    useFeaturePageContentV2(); // 20+ return keys
  return (
    <>
      <MapLayer center={mapCenter} zoom={mapZoom} ... />
      <Header onFocus={openSheet} ... />
      <BottomSheet sheetRef={sheetRef} cities={filteredCities} ... />
    </>
  );
};
```

```ts
// ❌ BAD — god hook file: unrelated concerns in one return type
export const useFeaturePageContentV2 = () => ({
  mapCenter, mapZoom, mapPlaces, sheetRef, openSheet, filteredCities,
  selectedPlace, searchValue, handleCityPick, showExploreFab, t, ...
});
```

## Where logic lives

| Concern | Owner |
|---|---|
| Sibling coordination (sheet ref, shared viewport, pick handlers) | `useFeatureState` inside Provider → context |
| Derived UI for one section (map markers, filtered list, overlay place) | That section's `useFeatureSection` hook |
| Pure transforms | `.util.ts` next to the hook that calls it |
| Page-wide state (selected city, auth gates) | Existing page context — do not duplicate in a god hook |

## Self-check before finishing a feature refactor

- [ ] No hook returns more than **10 keys** (if more → split or move derived data to consumer hooks)
- [ ] No parent component destructures **10+ values** from one hook to pass as props
- [ ] Every molecule under `molecules/` has its own `useMoleculeName.hook.ts`
- [ ] Feature/V2 context holds **coordination state only**, not all derived UI for every child
- [ ] Deleting one molecule does not require editing a 200-line god hook
